{"title": "Unsanitized user input in file path", "summary": " Using raw unsanitized input when forming filenames or file paths is bad practice. It can lead to path manipulation, by which attackers can gain access to resources outside of the intended scope. ", "description": "\nUsing raw unsanitized input when forming filenames or file paths is bad practice.\nIt can lead to path manipulation, by which attackers can gain access to resources outside of the intended scope.\n", "recommendations": "\n\u274c Avoid wherever possible\n\n\u2705 Validate expected file paths using `File` methods\n\n```ruby\n  path = File.expand(\"/home/\" + params[:resource_name])\n  if path.starts_with?(\"/home/\")\n    Dir.chdir(path)\n  else\n    # path is unexpected\n  end\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-73"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_path_using_user_input", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Path_Traversal"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}